messages.content: What does the baseball event code '7/F7LD' mean?
'7/F7LD' means a fly ball to left field, with the batter being put out as a result of a line drive that is caught.
'D8/L89XD+' signifies a double to centerfield, where the play is considered a line drive and hit to a particular spot in the outfield.
'13/G1S' means a ground ball to the pitcher which resulted in a single for the batter.
What does 'W' mean as a baseball event code?
'HR/F78XD.1-H' denotes a home run that was a fly ball to center-right field, including a line drive type out in the outfield, with a runner on first scoring.
'E6/TH/G6+.B-1' represents an error by the shortstop on the throw, where a runner advanced to first.
'8/L8D' signifies a line drive to center field that is a double.
'8/F8' means the batter is out on a fly ball to center field.
'S9/L9' represents a single, hit to right field via a line drive.
What does the baseball event code '6/G6' mean?
'6/G6' means a ground ball to the shortstop, resulting in an out.
'4/P4FO' means a pop fly to second base, with the batter being forced out.
'5/L5S' means a line drive to third base, resulting in a single.
'K23' indicates a strikeout, where the ball was dropped by the catcher but the batter was still out.
What does 'WP' mean as a baseball event code?
'HR/78' denotes a home run that was a fly ball hit to the center-right field.
'E5/TH/G5+.B-2' represents an error by the third baseman on the throw, where a runner advanced to second.
'9/F9' signifies a fly ball to right field, resulting in an out.
'3/G3U' means a ground ball to first base that is unassisted.
'S7/G7' represents a single, hit to left field via a ground ball.
'4/G43' means a ground ball to second, the batter being put out at first base.
'643/G643' represents a ground ball to short stop where the double play goes to second then first.
'FC/14/G' indicates a fielder's choice, with a ground ball to the pitcher who put out a runner.
'SB2' represents a stolen base of second base.
'CS2(2)' represents a runner caught stealing second base by the catcher.
'PO2(2)' means a runner was picked off at second base by the catcher.
'HP' indicates the batter was hit by the pitch.
'BK' represents a balk by the pitcher.
'7/F7LS' means a fly ball to left field, resulting in a sacrifice.
'13/G13DP' represents a ground ball to the pitcher, resulting in a double play.
'6/P6' signifies a pop up to the shortstop, resulting in an out.
'3/G34' means a ground ball to first base, resulting in an out at second base.
'S8/L8XD' represents a single via line drive to center field.
'E4/TH' represents an error by the second baseman on the throw, allowing a base runner to advance.
'5/F5S' means a fly ball to third that resulted in a single.
'2/P2FO' means a pop fly to the catcher which resulted in a force out.
'3/L3D' indicates a double via a line drive to the first base.
'S7/L7S' represents a single to left field via line drive.
'1/P1U' signifies a pop up to the pitcher that is unassisted.
'8/L8LS' means a line drive to center that was a sacrifice.
'9/F9DP' represents a fly ball to right field that results in a double play.
'4/G43/DP' represents a ground ball to second base which resulted in a double play.
What does 'SAC' mean as a baseball event code?
'7/G7SF' means a sacrifice fly to left field.
'1/G16' represents a ground ball to the pitcher, resulting in an out at short stop.
'6/F6LD' means a fly ball to the shortstop, that was a line drive and resulted in an out.
